## Step 2
The binomial distribution $b(n, p)$ has a mean $\mu = np$ and variance $\sigma^2 = np(1-p)$. Here, $p = 0.25$, so $\mu = n \times 0.25$ and $\sigma^2 = n \times 0.25 \times (1 - 0.25) = n \times 0.25 \times 0.75 = 0.1875n$.

