The integral $\int_{0}^{1} x^3(1-x)^6 dx$ is a beta function integral, $B(4, 7)$, because $\int_{0}^{1} x^{m-1}(1-x)^{n-1} dx = B(m, n)$. Here, $m = 4$ and $n = 7$, so $B(4, 7) = \int_{0}^{1} x^3(1-x)^6 dx$.

