The probability of drawing a red ball from the second urn is $\frac{x}{x+9}$, and the probability of drawing a blue ball from the second urn is $\frac{9}{x+9}$.

The probability of getting two balls of the same color is given by the sum of the probability of getting two red balls and the probability of getting two blue balls. So, we have:

